Margin

p { margin: 10px; }  

p {
 margin-left: 10px; 
 margin-right: 10px;
 margin-top: 10px;   
 margin-bottom: 10px; }

Color

Named colors
p { color: blue; }
b { color: transparent; }
i { color: lightgrey; }

rgb/rgba
p { color: rgb(10, 200, 255); }
p { color: rgb(0, 0, 0); } 
p { color: rgb(255, 255, 255); } 
b { color: rgba(10, 200, 255, 0.5); }

Hex code
p { color: #3A2BFF; }

px
'px' is short for 'pixel', which is a single dot on the screen. 
So text with  font-size:20px   is 20 pixels tall on-screen
. In actuality, due to browser zooming, retina displays, or other factors,
this may or may not match to 20 physical on-screen pixels.

px are useful for both horizontal and vertical dimensions. 

em

'em' is a typographic term that has come to the Web. On the Web, em units are 
usually used for vertical dimensions.  One 'em' maps to the height of one capital 
letter in the parent context. 
